	He also claimed that Kishan wasnt using a mobile phone since mid-February which was why the police werent able to trace him.         
	Ahmads assertion regarding scaling up the operation ties up with the recent review of the security forces conducted by CRPF DIG Alok Raj in Palamau. We need to re-assess our strategy based on intelligence, he had said.         
	Also, Chhattisgarh DGP Vishwa Ranjan held a meeting with the state police top brass on Monday to finalise plans for extending the operations to the Jharkhand-Chhattisgarh border.                                                                                                                                            
